sp.p:
I don’t mean to attempt to control your actions, but I am going to remain where I am for a
       week. I can’t see why this meeting should put us out; it is by no means a novel situation;
       for the first year after our separation we were always crossing each other’s paths.

You admit, then, that there is something terrible which is being kept secret from me. What
       can I do? I cannot, will not bear this suspense! I have lost all confidence in my husband;
       rely on it, Mr. Wylding, that Mrs. Tiverton is at the bottom of it all.
